<examples title="Creating forms by writing XForms by hand"
          xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <banner>
        The examples below have been created by writing XForms by hand. If you are not a developer, instead, you might
        be more interested in <xh:a href="./">creating forms with Form Builder</xh:a>.
    </banner>
    <example title="Espresso Order" href="/xforms-espresso/" img="/home/images/xforms-espresso-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/kubina/1469914113/">
        This example shows powerful aspect of XForms in a compact example:
        declarative binds, repeats, dynamic sets of items and dynamic rules.
    </example>
    <example title="XForms Bookcast" href="/xforms-bookcast/" img="/home/images/xforms-bookcast-small.jpg" portlet-exclude="true" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/osiatynska/3287986172/">
        The <xh:i>Bookcast</xh:i> app is part of the Orbeon <xh:a
        href="http://wiki.orbeon.com/forms/doc/developer-guide/orbeon-forms-xforms-tutorial">XForms tutorial</xh:a>.
        It shows simple XRX-style database access, repeats, and more.
    </example>
    <example title="XForms Todo" href="/xforms-todo/" img="/home/images/xforms-todo-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/childofwar/3097124543/">
        A todo-list example is a must-have for any web technology. And unmistakably, here is one, in XForms.
    </example>
    <example title="Flickr Resize" href="/xforms-flickr-resize/" img="/home/images/xforms-flickr-resize-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/seanmolin/5638588326/">
        Use an XForms submission to do a search on Flickr through their REST API, and uses a slider to dynamically
        change the size of the images.
    </example>
    <example title="XForms Sandbox" href="/xforms-sandbox/" img="/home/images/xforms-sandbox-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/foreverphoto/2467694199/">
        Play with built-in XForms samples, or test your own samples by uploading or linking to them.
    </example>
    <example title="XPath Sandbox" href="/sandbox-transformations/xpath/" img="/home/images/xpath-sandbox-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/vinothchandar/6820565620/" portlet-exclude="true">
        Test XPath expressions and see instantly, as you type, what they evaluate to.
    </example>
    <example title="XForms Translate" href="/xforms-translate/" img="/home/images/xforms-translate-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/horiavarlan/4290551550/">
        Try as-you-type translation by screen scraping Google Translate.
    </example>
    <example title="Flickr Search" href="/xforms-jsp/flickr-search/" img="/home/images/xforms-flickr-search-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/vladdythephotogeek/4886804743/" portlet-exclude="true" >
        Simple Flickr search with XForms generated by a JSP.
    </example>
    <example title="Guess the Number" href="/xforms-jsp/guess-the-number/" img="/home/images/xforms-wizard-switch-small.jpg" size="4"
             source="http://www.flickr.com/photos/mcgraths/3248483447/" portlet-exclude="true" >
        Simple number guess game with XForms generated by a JSP.
    </example>
</examples>